# Claude Code - Anthropic's Official CLI

I'm Claude Code, Anthropic's official command-line interface for Claude. I help developers build with Claude through the terminal.

## Key Resources

Based on the documentation overview, here are the main areas I can help you with:

### Getting Started
- **[Quickstart Guide](https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/get-started.md)** - Get started with Claude
- **[Intro to Claude](https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/intro.md)** - Introduction to Claude's capabilities

### Building with Claude
- **[Models Overview](https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/about-claude/models/overview.md)** - Available Claude models
- **[Choosing a Model](https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/about-claude/models/choosing-a-model.md)** - Select the right model for your use case
- **[Messages API](https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/build-with-claude/working-with-messages.md)** - Core API for interacting with Claude

### Prompt Engineering

content.content:
# Claude Code overview

> Learn about Claude Code, Anthropic's agentic coding tool that lives in your terminal and helps you turn ideas into code faster than ever before.

## Get started in 30 seconds

Prerequisites:

* A [Claude.ai](https://claude.ai) (recommended) or [Claude Console](https://console.anthropic.com/) account

**Install Claude Code:**

To install Claude Code, use one of the following methods:

<Tabs>
  <Tab title="Native Install (Recommended)">
    **macOS, Linux, WSL:**

    ```bash  theme={null}
    curl -fsSL https://claude.ai/install.sh | bash
    ```

    **Windows PowerShell:**

    ```powershell  theme={null}
    irm https://claude.ai/install.ps1 | iex
    ```

    **Windows CMD:**

    ```batch  theme={null}
    curl -fsSL https://claude.ai/install.cmd -o install.cmd && install.cmd && del install.cmd
    ```
  </Tab>

  <Tab title="Homebrew">
    ```sh  theme={null}
    brew install --cask claude-code
    ```
  </Tab>

  <Tab title="NPM">
    If you have [Node.js 18 or newer installed](https://nodejs.org/en/download/):

    ```sh  theme={null}
    npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code
    ```
  </Tab>
</Tabs>

**Start using Claude Code:**

```bash  theme={null}
cd your-project
claude
```

You'll be prompted to log in on first use. That's it! [Continue with Quickstart (5 minutes) ](/en/quickstart)

<Tip>
  Claude Code automatically keeps itself up to date. See [advanced setup](/en/setup) for installation options, manual updates, or uninstallation instructions. Visit [troubleshooting](/en/troubleshooting) if you hit issues.
</Tip>

## What Claude Code does for you

* **Build features from descriptions**: Tell Claude what you want to build in plain English. It will make a plan, write the code, and ensure it works.
* **Debug and fix issues**: Describe a bug or paste an error message. Claude Code will analyze your codebase, identify the problem, and implement a fix.
* **Navigate any codebase**: Ask anything about your team's codebase, and get a thoughtful answer back. Claude Code maintains awareness of your entire project structure, can find up-to-date information from the web, and with [MCP](/en/mcp) can pull from external data sources like Google Drive, Figma, and Slack.
* **Automate tedious tasks**: Fix fiddly lint issues, resolve merge conflicts, and write release notes. Do all this in a single command from your developer machines, or automatically in CI.

## Why developers love Claude Code

* **Works in your terminal**: Not another chat window. Not another IDE. Claude Code meets you where you already work, with the tools you already love.
* **Takes action**: Claude Code can directly edit files, run commands, and create commits. Need more? [MCP](/en/mcp) lets Claude read your design docs in Google Drive, update your tickets in Jira, or use *your* custom developer tooling.
* **Unix philosophy**: Claude Code is composable and scriptable. `tail -f app.log | claude -p "Slack me if you see any anomalies appear in this log stream"` *works*. Your CI can run `claude -p "If there are new text strings, translate them into French and raise a PR for @lang-fr-team to review"`.
* **Enterprise-ready**: Use the Claude API, or host on AWS or GCP. Enterprise-grade [security](/en/security), [privacy](/en/data-usage), and [compliance](https://trust.anthropic.com/) is built-in.

## Next steps

<CardGroup>
  <Card title="Quickstart" icon="rocket" href="/en/quickstart">
    See Claude Code in action with practical examples
  </Card>

  <Card title="Common workflows" icon="graduation-cap" href="/en/common-workflows">
    Step-by-step guides for common workflows
  </Card>

  <Card title="Troubleshooting" icon="wrench" href="/en/troubleshooting">
    Solutions for common issues with Claude Code
  </Card>

  <Card title="IDE setup" icon="laptop" href="/en/vs-code">
    Add Claude Code to your IDE
  </Card>
</CardGroup>

## Additional resources

<CardGroup>
  <Card title="About Claude Code" icon="sparkles" href="https://claude.com/product/claude-code">
    Learn more about Claude Code on claude.com
  </Card>

  <Card title="Build with the Agent SDK" icon="code-branch" href="https://docs.claude.com/en/docs/agent-sdk/overview">
    Create custom AI agents with the Claude Agent SDK
  </Card>

  <Card title="Host on AWS or GCP" icon="cloud" href="/en/third-party-integrations">
    Configure Claude Code with Amazon Bedrock or Google Vertex AI
  </Card>

  <Card title="Settings" icon="gear" href="/en/settings">
    Customize Claude Code for your workflow
  </Card>

  <Card title="Commands" icon="terminal" href="/en/cli-reference">
    Learn about CLI commands and controls
  </Card>

  <Card title="Reference implementation" icon="code" href="https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/tree/main/.devcontainer">
    Clone our development container reference implementation
  </Card>

  <Card title="Security" icon="shield" href="/en/security">
    Discover Claude Code's safeguards and best practices for safe usage
  </Card>

  <Card title="Privacy and data usage" icon="lock" href="/en/data-usage">
    Understand how Claude Code handles your data
  </Card>
</CardGroup>


---

> To find navigation and other pages in this documentation, fetch the llms.txt file at: https://code.claude.com/docs/llms.txt

Based on the search results, I can provide you with comprehensive information about Claude Code's browser automation and web browsing capabilities with Playwright in 2026:

## Browser Automation Capabilities

Claude Code combined with Playwright's Model Context Protocol (MCP) transforms browser automation and testing, enabling AI-assisted web interactions and test automation.

### Integration Methods

There are several ways to integrate Playwright with Claude Code:

1. **Official Microsoft Playwright MCP Server**: A Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that provides browser automation capabilities using Playwright, enabling LLMs to interact with web pages through structured accessibility snapshots

2. **Playwright Skills/Plugins**: A Claude Skill that enables Claude to write and execute any Playwright automation on-the-fly, with Claude autonomously deciding when to use this skill based on browser automation needs

3. **Computer Use Integration**: Code to connect a Playwright browser to Claude's computer use capabilities, enabling browser interaction for agent tasks

### Key Features

A visible Chrome browser window, controlled by Claude Code, opens when using Playwright MCP. Authentication is easy: Claude can show you a login page, then you login yourself with your own credentials, with cookies persisting for the duration of the session(no content)The MCP Playwright server provides developers with browser automation capabilities accessible directly from Claude Code to create smooth interactions between AI reasoning and executing JavaScript in a real browser environment

### Setup Process

You can use the official microsoft/playwright-mcp server with Claude Code by running a simple command, and then Playwright will be available when you run claude

The integration enables various automation tasks including testing pages, filling forms, taking screenshots, checking responsive design, validating UX, testing login flows, and automating general browser tasks.

Based on my research, I can provide you with comprehensive information about Claude Code's browser automation capabilities.

## Browser Automation in Claude Code

Claude Code does **not have built-in browser automation capabilities**. However, you can add browser automation through several integration methods:

### Official Approach: Playwright MCP Server

The recommended way to add browser automation to Claude Code is through the **Microsoft Playwright MCP Server**, which provides Model Context Protocol (MCP) integration. This gives Claude Code access to Playwright's browser automation features.

Key features of the Playwright MCP integration:

- **Structured accessibility snapshots** for web page interaction
- **Visible Chrome browser window** that you can control through Claude Code
- **Authentication support** with persistent cookies for the session duration
- **Various automation tasks** including:
  - Testing pages
  - Filling forms
  - Taking screenshots
  - Checking responsive design
  - Validating UX
  - Testing login flows
  - Automating general browser interactions

### Alternative Browser Automation Options

The ecosystem has created several community solutions for browser automation with Claude Code:

1. **Playwright Skills/Plugins** - Community-created Claude Skills that enable autonomous Playwright automation where Claude writes and executes custom browser scripts
2. **Computer Use Integration** - Code connecting Playwright browsers to Claude's computer use capabilities
3. **Other Browser Tools** - Puppeteer or other browser automation frameworks can be integrated through custom MCP servers

### How to Set Up Playwright MCP

To use browser automation in Claude Code, you would:

1. Configure the official microsoft/playwright-mcp MCP server in your Claude Code setup
2. Once configured, Playwright tools become available when you run `claude`
3. Claude can then interact with websites through the browser

### Important Notes

- Claude Code uses **Playwright specifically** (not direct Selenium or other tools) for the official integrations
- Browser automation is not native to Claude Code but is added through MCP servers
- The Playwright integration opens a visible Chrome window, allowing you to see what Claude is doing
- You maintain control over authentication - you can log in yourself while Claude watches

This architecture allows Claude Code to browse the web and interact with websites, but it requires explicitly setting up the Playwright MCP server rather than having it as a built-in feature.

Sources:
- [GitHub - lackeyjb/playwright-skill](https://github.com/lackeyjb/playwright-skill)
- [GitHub - executeautomation/mcp-playwright](https://github.com/executeautomation/mcp-playwright)
- [GitHub - microsoft/playwright-mcp](https://github.com/microsoft/playwright-mcp)
- [Using Playwright MCP with Claude Code - Simon Willison's TILs](https://til.simonwillison.net/claude-code/playwright-mcp-claude-code)
- [Using Playwright MCP with Claude Code - DevGuide.dev](https://devguide.dev/blog/using-playwright-mcp-with-claude-code)
